xs-vector-definition.description: Initialise a vector with the given X, Y, Z components

xs-vector-get-x.description: Get the X component of the specified vector. Returns a float value

xs-vector-get-y.description: Get the Y component of the specified vector. Returns a float value

xs-vector-get-z.description: Get the Z component of the specified vector. Returns a float value

xs-vector-set-x.description: Return a new vector with the X component of the given vector changed to the given value.

xs-vector-set-y.description: Return a new vector with the Y component of the given vector changed to the given value.

xs-vector-set-z.description: Return a new vector with the Z component of the given vector changed to the given value.

xs-vector-set.description: Return a vector with the given X, Y and Z components.

xs-vector-length.description: Return the length of the given vector.

xs-vector-normalize.description: Returns a unit vector along the direction of the given vector.
